class Solution {
    public String finalString(String s) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder("");
        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
            if(s.charAt(i)=='i') sb.reverse();
            else sb.append(s.charAt(i));
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
}

TC - O(N^2) => n is for iteration and k is the occurence of i, since reverse() is O(n)

It might optimise if convert string to character array or ArrayList
